<P>
   AT&AMP;T-BRAND (New York) _ After more than 100 years, the AT&AMP;T
brand is one of the most recognized in the world, a hallmark of
corporate stability and might. It is no longer enough. On Tuesday,
for the first time since the AT&AMP;T Corp. was founded in 1885, the
company introduced a brand that does not mention AT&AMP;T: the Lucky
Dog Phone Co. Television advertisements for the ``new'' company
began running on Tuesday in 18 big markets, including New York and
Los Angeles. Just as the advertisements for Red Dog beer do not
mention the Miller Brewing Co., which makes it, and those for the
10-10-321 phone service do not mention MCI Worldcom Inc., which
provides it, the Lucky Dog advertisements do not mention AT&AMP;T. By
Seth Schiesel.
</P>
<P>
   ESCAPE-SAILBOAT (Undated) _ There is something familiar about
the slogan on Escape Sailboat Co.'s Web site: The Sailboat for the
Rest of Us. If the phrase calls to mind Apple Computer's famous
1980s pitch for the Macintosh, ``a computer for the rest of us,''
well, that's fine with Peter Johnstone, Escape's president and
co-founder. After all, the Macintosh redefined the personal
computer industry, and Johnstone aims to do the same for sailing.
By Lawrence M. Fisher.
</P>
