<P>
   CHRYSLER-MARKETPLACE (Detroit) _ Chrysler Corp., with a
particularly bad reputation for running into trouble during
recessions, seemed last spring to have found a nifty way around
investors' distrust. It agreed to merge with Daimler-Benz AG, which
trades at a higher multiple in the German market, where investors
have tended to look more favorably on auto stocks. But with
Daimler's stock plunging since the deal's announcement _ and with
auto stocks faring poorly this autumn in the United States too _
Chrysler shareholders are feeling much less prosperous. By Keith
Bradsher.
