<P>
   MCCARTY-COLUMN _ DAYTON, Ohio _ I scratched my head, wondering
how my most significant achievements would translate into granite:
``She kept an epically messy desk.'' ``She got her son to school on
time one morning in 1997.'' Ah, to be among that roster of
Daytonians, who, though obscure in name, achieved things that are
world-renowned and easy to summarize. (McCarty, Dayton Daily News)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   KELSO-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ I'm so smart I need an extra
skull for all these bright ideas. I have the solution to the
gang/dress code problem. Rather than make law-abiding high school
kids change clothes, why not make the gang members dress stylishly
like they used to? (Kelso, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
