director Kenny Leon leading the celebs in a post-show toast in
Woodruff galleria. (Eldredge, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8
p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   AIDA-MUSIC _ How the Elton-Tim Rice songs hold up as
radio-friendly pop product, stage show aside. Trying for details of
soundtrack. (Dollar, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS-NOTES _ Congressman John Lewis and novelist Elizabeth Cox
are the winners of this year's Lillian Smith Awards; Atlanta writer
Iris Johansen on her new thriller about a forensic sculptor; Book
magazine makes its debut. (O'Briant, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS-ROCKETBOYS _ DAYTON, Ohio _ When Homer Hickam Jr. tells a
room full of schoolchildren that ``if you want anything badly
enough, and you'll work for it, you can do it,'' the words ring
with hard-won truth. Hickam, 55, was only 14 when he and his
friends in a small West Virginia coal town spotted Sputnik winking
across the sky one night and were inspired to build a rocket of
their own. (DeBrosse, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SCIENCE/MEDICINE
</P>
<P>
   SPACEPROGRAM-CLOSING _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Dayton may greet the 100th
anniversary of powered flight by losing a key part of the space
program it pioneered in the 1960s: nuclear generators and heaters
for deep space probes. (Gaffney, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   BREAST _ ATLANTA _ In support of October as Breast Cancer
Awareness month, companies have created exclusive cosmetics and
apparel to wear or give as reminders of this disease, which kills
43,000 American women each year. And stores are offering special
promotions. (Johnson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   BETRAYAL _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Although Linda Tripp didn't
invent betrayal _ Pontius Pilate, Brutus and Benedict Arnold beat
her to the punch _ she certainly excelled at it. But despite her
deception (complete with wire and tapped phone), Tripp doesn't
deserve all the credit. Monica Lewinsky, after all, played into her
hand. (Grantham, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   CREDIT-DEBT _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Buy now, pay never.
</P>
<P>
   That's how more Americans than ever think _ if they think at all
_ when they pay with plastic. It's one of the big reasons we set
records for personal bankruptcies three years in a row, and why
Congress is determined to stop the streak. (Kalajian, Palm Beach
Post) MOVED.
</P>
