apparel to wear or give as reminders of this disease, which kills
43,000 American women each year. And stores are offering special
promotions. (Johnson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   BETRAYAL _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Although Linda Tripp didn't
invent betrayal _ Pontius Pilate, Brutus and Benedict Arnold beat
her to the punch _ she certainly excelled at it. But despite her
deception (complete with wire and tapped phone), Tripp doesn't
deserve all the credit. Monica Lewinsky, after all, played into her
hand. (Grantham, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   CREDIT-DEBT _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Buy now, pay never.
</P>
<P>
   That's how more Americans than ever think _ if they think at all
_ when they pay with plastic. It's one of the big reasons we set
records for personal bankruptcies three years in a row, and why
Congress is determined to stop the streak. (Kalajian, Palm Beach
Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   _ with DEBT-SIDE _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Five years ago, Len
Rodriguez's life was moving far too fast to allow even a glance at
a credit-card balance that was accelerating faster than his red
Corvette. ``You want to impress everybody,'' he said. ``It was a
mistake.'' Then his income took a sudden, sharp drop. What happened
to Rodriguez is typical of problems faced by many middle-income
people who leave themselves nothing to fall back on. (Kalajian,
Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   DEPRESSED-KIDS _ DAYTON, Ohio _ When their mild-mannered
16-year-old daughter suddenly became the teen-ager from hell _
defiant, belligerent, into drugs and premarital sex _ Bob and Doris
Riley (not their actual names) blamed the bad crowd she had started
running with. But a family counselor soon found an underlying cause
the Dayton parents had never suspected _ their daughter was
suffering from clinical depression. (DeBrosse, Dayton Daily News)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD
</P>
<P>
   COOKING-SCHOOLS _ Back to Cooking School. Cooking classes are
booming throughout metro Atlanta, with instructions available for
every kind of cook, from the beginner to the advanced, the
vegetarian to the cake decorator. We sit in on some of the most
popular classes and talk to students and instructors, then offer a
listing of schools with descriptions and how to sign up. (Walker,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS. ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-RECIPES _ Recipe page to go with cooking schools story
centerpieced on AJC weekly food section. (Walker, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-RECIPESWAP _A weekly recipe exchange column. This week:
Poundcake. (Langhenry, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-CYBERSPICE _ A weekly column looking at the plethora of
recipes on the Internet. This week: garlic. (Parham, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
