<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Thursday, Oct. 8, and thereafter. If you have any questions, please
call Tina May at (206) 448-8355.
</P>
<P>
   ECONOMY-COLUMN-RAMSEY (Seattle) SEATTLE _ Official economists
are often among the last to predict recessions. Thus it was notable
Monday when Oregon's economist, Paul Warner, said the chance of a
U.S. recession ``is definitely growing and is getting close to 50
percent.''
</P>
<P>
   By Bruce Ramsey. (story will move in the ``f'' category)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-07-98 1256EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
