<SLUG> BC-TAPAS-FOOD-RECIPES-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
RECIPES FOR MAKING TAPAS 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By ANN CRISWELL 
c.1998 Houston Chronicle 
<TEXT>
<P>
   CEVICHE SOLERO
</P>
<P>
   From ``Houston Is Cooking At Home'' by Ann Criswell (Houston
Gourmet, $21.95).
</P>
<P>
   INGREDIENTS: 1 pound each: shrimp, peeled and deveined, and
boneless, skinless snapper fillets &QL; 
1 tablespoon each: olive oil, fresh orange juice and white vinegar &QL; 
2 cups fresh lime juice &QL; 
1 tablespoon each, chopped: garlic and red onion &QL; 
{ cup diced red bell pepper &QL; 
1 jalapeno with seeds, diced &QL; 
pinch of ground cumin &QL; 
1 teaspoon salt &QL; 
1 tablespoon chopped cilantro leaves &QL; 
2 tablespoons passion fruit puree (see note) &QL; 
endive, lettuce, bell pepper strips and lime slices for garnish &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Cut shrimp and snapper into 1-inch pieces. Cook shrimp in
boiling water to cover 1 minute. Drain, cover and refrigerate until
chilled. Combine snapper, oil, orange juice, vinegar, lime juice,
garlic, onion, bell pepper, jalapeo, cumin, salt, cilantro and
fruit pure in large bowl. Add shrimp; cover and marinate in
refrigerator at least 6 hours. Serve on endive and lettuce
garnished with bell pepper and lime. Makes 8 servings.
</P>
<P>
   Note: Passion fruit puree is available in the freezer section of
many grocery outlets.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   SHRIMP WITH GARLIC (``Camarones al Mojo de Ajo'')
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   INGREDIENTS: \ cup olive oil &QL; 
1 tablespoon chopped garlic &QL; 
3 shrimp (21-25 count), peeled and deveined &QL; 
1 teaspoon each: red bell pepper flakes and fresh lime juice &QL; 
{ teaspoon salt &QL; 
8 cilantro leaves &QL; 
2 tablespoons diced tomatoes &QL; 
1 tablespoon chopped green onion &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Heat oil. Add garlic and cook until golden brown. Add shrimp;
cook 30 seconds. Add pepper flakes, lime juice, salt, cilantro,
tomatoes and green onion. Cook until shrimp is pink. Makes 1
serving.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CUCUMBER SALAD
</P>
<P>
   INGREDIENTS:1 { pounds cucumbers, peeled and cut in half
lengthwise &QL; 
} to 1 cup olive oil &QL; 
{ cup rice wine vinegar &QL; 
\ cup each: fresh lime juice and chopped garlic &QL; 
1 tablespoon red pepper flakes &QL; 
4 tablespoons chopped fresh oregano &QL; 
2 teaspoons salt &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   To seed cucumber halves, hollow them out like boats. Slice.
Combine oil, vinegar, lime juice, garlic, pepper flakes, oregano
and salt; mix with cucumber slices. Makes 8 servings.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   SPICY POTATOES (``Papas Bravas'')
</P>
<P>
   INGREDIENTS: 4 tablespoons oil &QL; 
2 teaspoons chopped garlic &QL; 
\ cup diced red onion &QL; 
4 links Spanish chorizo (10 ounces), sliced &QL; 
\ cup sliced green onion &QL; 
} cup canned or jarred roasted sweet red pepper slices, drained &QL; 
1 tablespoon salt (optional) &QL; 
1 teaspoon red pepper flakes &QL; 
2 cups chicken stock &QL; 
1 teaspoon mixed fresh herbs (oregano, thyme, black pepper) &QL; 
16 medium-size new potatoes, cooked and cut in quarters &QL; 
2 teaspoons Mexican hot sauce (Cholula specified) &QL; 
1 cup chopped mushrooms &QL; 
20 leaves (small bunch) cilantro leaves &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Heat oil in large frying pan; cook garlic and red onion until
golden brown. Add chorizo and cook 3 minutes. Add green onion, red
peppers, salt, pepper flakes, stock, herbs and potatoes. Cook over
medium-high heat 8 to 10 minutes until sausage is browned. Add hot
sauce, mushrooms and cilantro about 2 minutes before dish is done;
cook until heated through. Serve in a bowl with fork and spoon and
with bread for dipping if desired. Makes 8 servings.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   GARLIC SHRIMP (``Gambas al Ajillo'')
</P>
<P>
   INGREDIENTS: 2 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil &QL; 
6 medium shrimp, peeled &QL; 
1 tablespoon each: chopped garlic and fresh lemon juice &QL; 
\ teaspoon crushed red pepper &QL; 
Pinch of salt &QL; 
1 tablespoon chopped fresh parsley &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Heat oil in skillet. Add shrimp and cook 30 seconds. Add garlic,
lemon juice, pepper, salt and parsley. Cook 1 minute until shrimp
are opaque. Makes 1 to 2 servings.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   EGGPLANT SAUTEED WITH GARLIC(``Berenjenas a la Plancha con
Ajo'')
</P>
<P>
   INGREDIENTS: 2 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil &QL; 
\ cup diced onion &QL; 
1 tablespoon chopped garlic &QL; 
1 pound eggplant, cut in large cubes &QL; 
\ teaspoon each: salt and black pepper &QL; 
1 tablespoon each: fresh lemon juice and chopped parsley &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Heat oil in frying pan. Add onion, garlic, eggplant, salt,
pepper, lemon juice and parsley. Saut 2 minutes. Makes 2 to 3
servings.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CATALAN SPINACH BARCELONA (``Espinacas a la Catalana'')
</P>
<P>
   INGREDIENTS:3 tablespoons raisins or sultanas &QL; 
4 {(scant) pounds fresh spinach, washed, trimmed and stemmed &QL; 
2 ounces (4 tablespoons) olive oil &QL; 
1 garlic clove, peeled and chopped &QL; 
3 tablespoons pine nuts &QL; 
Salt and pepper to taste &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Soak raisins in warm water while preparing and cooking spinach.
Boil spinach in a very small amount of water, or just the water
that clings to the leaves, 5 minutes. Drain well. Press in a
strainer or between 2 plates to remove excess water. Chop spinach
coarsely. Drain raisins and cut them in half.
</P>
<P>
   Heat oil in frying pan and saute garlic. After 1 minute, add
spinach, pine nuts and raisins. Season with salt and pepper; saute
5 minutes. Makes 4 servings. &QL; 
 &QL; 
XXXXEND OF STORY &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
