billion, of public money into solvent banks, a key ingredient
missing from the package of bank bills passed last week. Japanese
stocks surge 6.2 percent, their biggest gain this year, and the yen
rises sharply against the dollar. By Sheryl WuDunn.
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ At 1:20 p.m., the industrial average was up
12 points. Elsewhere, prices increased 6.2 percent in Tokyo and 2.4
percent in Hong Kong. They fell 2.9 percent in Frankfurt, 0.2
percent in London and 0.7 percent in Brazil. They rose half a
percent in Mexico. On the American debt market, the long bond was
down 1 13/32 points at midday, with the yield at 4.82 percent. By
Robert D. Hershey Jr.
