<HEADLINE>
PRIVACY PROTECTION 
</HEADLINE>
   (af)  
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Who knows what secrets lurk on your hard drive? With luck, and
with the following security programs, only you do. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PGP 5.5 Windows 95/98/NT and Macintosh OS 7.5.3 and newer Free
for individual, noncommercial use in the United States and Canada
http://www.pgp.com/products/pgpfreeware.cgi Philip R. Zimmermanns
Pretty Good Privacy, or PGP, is one of the world's most widely used
encryption programs for personal computers, so good, in fact, that
the United States government contends it is as potent a military
weapon as a jet fighter or a cruise missile.
</P>
<P>
   A similar, commercial version called PGP Personal Privacy 6.0 is
available for $39.95 from McAfee Software, Santa Clara, Calif.,
(408) 988-3832, www.mcafee.com &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Norton Your Eyes Only 4.1 Windows 95/98/NT About $75
www.symantec.com (800) 441-7234 Norton Your Eyes Only performs a
variety of password-protected security functions. It can be set to
blank the screen and lock the the computer if the user steps away
for a minute or to prevent unauthorized users from booting the
machine. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   RSA SecurPC Windows 95/98/NT $59 Security Dynamics Technologies,
Inc., Bedford, Mass. (800) 732-8743 Intended more for small office
use, SecurPC links with the Windows Explorer file management system
to automatically and transparently lock disks and files with
128-bit encryption, but it allows the keys to be shared with
administrators. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Cookie Crusher Windows $15 shareware (www.zdnet.com/swlib,
www.shareware.com, etc.) Cookies are small tracking files that a
Web site installs on your hard drive. The cookie can contain
technical and personal information, including a history of the Web
pages you have visited. These utilities enable the user to accept
or reject cookies. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BCWipe Windows $15 shareware (www.download.com,
www.zdnet.com/swlib and others). For those who prefer not to use an
encryption package, BCWipe provides military-grade file and disk
wiping to make sure deleted files are really erased.
</P>
</TEXT>
