<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    This Weekend on TV
 &HT;    By Bob Longino
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   FRIDAY
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Hard Rock Live'' 7 p.m. EDT on VH1 _ Trisha Yearwood, Don
Henley and the Mavericks perform in this taped, hourlong show.
Yearwood's songs include ``There Goes My Baby,'' ``How Do I Live''
and ``Hearts in Armor'' (with Henley). Among tunes the Mavericks
perform is ``All You Ever Do Is Bring Me Down.''
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The Best of `Dinner &AMP; a Movie''' 8:05 p.m. EDT on TBS _
Clips from the first three years of shows with culinary cutups
Annabelle Gurwitch and Paul Gilmartin. This is followed by the
100th episode of the series, with Steven Spielberg's 1981 adventure
film ``Raiders of the Lost Ark'' (8:35 p.m. EDT). The recipe: Super
Cheesy Spielburgers.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Universal Horror'' 8 p.m. EDT on Turner Classic Movies _
Kenneth Branagh narrates this new two-hour documentary about horror
movies from Universal, including ``King Kong,'' ``The Invisible
Man'' and ``Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde.'' Among those interviewed: Fay
Wray, Gloria Stuart and Ray Bradbury.
</P>
<P>
   -- The horror, the horror _ Right after the documentary, TCM
offers up a film fright fest that lasts all weekend. Among the
offerings: 1931's ``Frankenstein'' (10 p.m. EDT Friday), 1935's
``The Bride of Frankenstein'' (1:30 a.m. EDT late night Friday),
1931's ``Dracula'' (8 p.m. EDT Saturday), 1932's ``The Mummy''
(9:30 p.m. EDT Saturday), 1933's ``The Invisible Man'' (11 p.m. EDT
Saturday), 1941's ``The Wolf Man'' (12:30 a.m. EDT late night
Saturday), 1925's ``The Phantom of the Opera'' (8 p.m. EDT Sunday)
and 1923's ``The Hunchback of Notre Dame'' (midnight EDT Sunday).
</P>
<P>
   SUNDAY
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The Secret Life of Cats'' 7 p.m. EDT on TBS _ What exactly
does your furry little friend do _ besides beg for food from
neighbors _ after she exits your back door? This special looks at
felines as the aggressive hunters they are.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Cold War'' 8 p.m. EDT on CNN _ This installment looks at
the Marshall Plan and the Truman Doctrine.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Crime and Punishment'' (1992) 9 p.m. EDT on NBC _ NBC's
adaptation of Dostoyevsky's critically acclaimed novel explores
murder, guilt and justice. Patrick Dempsey plays a young Russian
student who believes that extraordinary people _ such as himself _
have the right to commit any crime that helps society. Co-stars
include Ben Kingsley and Julie Delpy.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Vietnam: The Soldier's Story'' 9 p.m. EDT on The Learning
Channel _ A six-part documentary (two parts air tonight) detailing
veterans' accounts of covert operations, important battles and the
treatment of prisoners of war. Continues Monday and Tuesday at 9
p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
