</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-VIDEO-REVIEWS08-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    MINI VIEWS: Reviews of the latest on video
 &HT;    By Steve Murray and Eleanor Ringel
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   -- ``Lost in Space'' (PG-13) _ A movie that has all the flash
and depth of the latest Nintendo game. Based on the campy 1960s TV
show, ``Lost in Space'' throws in vicious space spiders, genetic
monsters, confusing time-travel elements and heavy doses of family
values. The film stars William Hurt, Mimi Rogers and Heather
Graham. There's also Gary Oldman as the evil Dr. Smith and
``Friends'' hunk Matt LeBlanc as the arrogant pilot Major West.
Predictably, the movie has an open ending, suitable for sequels.
Grade: C+
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Character'' (unrated) _ The 1997 Oscar winner for best
foreign language film, this dour but compelling Dutch import is
laden with Dickensian incident and a Kafkaesque sense of fate. Set
in Rotterdam in the 1920s, it's the tale of a relentless war waged
between a formidable father (Jan Decleir) and his illegitimate son
(Fedja van Huet). Not exactly a lighthearted romp, but so much
happens that you barely notice. Grade: B+
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
