<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Spotlight on. . . Michael Douglas (``A Perfect Murder'')
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``The China Syndrome'': Getting the nuclear scoop with Jane
Fonda.
</P>
<P>
   ``Romancing the Stone'': Swashbuckling south of the border with
romance writer Kathleen Turner.
</P>
<P>
   ``Wall Street'': Teaching the 1980s mantra ``greed is good,''
and winning an Oscar for it.
</P>
<P>
   ``Fatal Attraction'': Doing something besides cooking in the
kitchen with Glenn Close.
</P>
<P>
   ``The War of the Roses'': Reteaming with Turner _ not for
romance, but brutal divorce in this black comedy.
</P>
<P>
   ``Basic Instinct'': Investigating and romancing bisexual murder
suspect Sharon Stone; you'd think he would've learned his lesson
from Glenn Close.
</P>
<P>
   ``Falling Down'': Going postal in Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   ``The American President'': Romance in the Oval Office with
Annette Bening _ a lobbyist, not an intern.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Ghost and the Darkness'': Hunting big cats with Val
Kilmer.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Game'': What do you give a man who has everything? A major
mind trip.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
