<SLUG> BC-LEGACY-TV-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
A `LEGACY' OF PROGRAMMING HISTORICAL FARE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By KEITH MARDER 
c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ &UR;  &LR; Maybe it was a strategic move on the part of the
United Paramount Network.
</P>
<P>
   Four days after the debut of ``The Secret Diaries of Desmond
Pfeiffer,'' the farce of a comedy that has come under fire for its
depiction of the Civil War era, the network premieres its other
period piece, ``Legacy,'' set in post-Civil War Kentucky.
</P>
<P>
   And this one _ so far _ doesn't go anywhere near controversial
issues such as slavery.
</P>
<P>
   ``Legacy,'' a beautiful video postcard with a melodic
Irish-music soundtrack, focuses on the Logan family, an earnest and
honest brood that traces its lineage back to County Cork, Ireland.
The first Logans stepped foot on U.S. soil in the late 1700s and
began a legacy of helping those less fortunate than themselves.
</P>
<P>
   Enter Jeremy Bradford (Ron Melendez), a scheming, larcenous,
city-slicker orphan from New York City.
</P>
<P>
   This soap opera drama, which is an odd hybrid of ``Bonanza'' and
``Dallas,'' has enough conflict to keep it going awhile.
</P>
<P>
   But as is often the problem with large ensemble dramas, it's
sometimes hard to keep people straight. Sean (Grayson McCouch) and
Clay (Jeremy Garrett) Logan look so much alike, it's hard to
distinguish between the brothers.
</P>
<P>
   This good-looking show with a great-looking _ and sometimes
look-alike _ cast may be at times sappy and predictable, but it
could find an audience. However, it still seems an odd choice for
UPN, and an even odder choice to pair with ``The Love Boat: The
Next Wave,'' the network's only other Friday show.
</P>
<P>
   THE SHOW: ``Legacy.''
</P>
<P>
   WHAT: A family drama about a close-knit Irish brood in
post-Civil War Kentucky.
</P>
<P>
   THE STARS: Brett Cullen, Grayson McCouch, Jeremy Garrett, Lea
Moreno, Sarah Rayne, Ron Melendez, Lisa Sheridan.
</P>
<P>
   WHERE: UPN (KCOP, Channel 13).
</P>
<P>
   WHEN: 8 p.m. Fridays.
</P>
<P>
   OUR RATING: 3 Stars.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
