CLINTON-PASTOR (Washington) - Ed Pastor, Arizona's sole Democrat in
Congress and considered a safe seat, announced Wednesday that he
will vote for a limited inquiry to impeach President Clinton.
Pastor's position reflects that of the Democratic leadership's new
strategy. Because they know they cannot stop the Republican drive
for an open-ended inquiry, they are fighting for an alternative
that would confine the impeachment inquiry to the Starr report on
the Lewinsky matter. The same leaders are prodding the White House
to drop its opposition, too. So it now appears that the vote today
(Thursday) will probably authorize a long, detailed examination of
