10-07 -- Rep. Charles Schumer in Rochester recently. Schumer and
Sen. Alfonse D'Amato are locked in an extraordinarily tight race
for the U.S. Senate. The outcome apparently rests with a small
group of undecided voters, many of whom are not yet paying
attention to the contest, a statewide New York Times/CBS News Poll
has found. (James Estrin/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT31) WASHINGTON, England -- Oct. 07, 1998 --
BRITAIN-MONETARY, 10-07 -- Britain's economy is slowing down. ``We
are much more vulnerable than most other regions,'' says Hugh
Morgan Williams, head of Canford Audio, shown in his company's
warehouse. In the last year, he says, export earnings by his modest
company in this blustery factory park in northeastern England have
fallen because the strong British pound makes his products more
expensive for foreign buyers. (Jonathan Player/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
