keyboard so children 3 and older can use ``tools'' when prompted by
a CD-ROM character named Tonka Joe. The child is given no choice
here, no goal, no understanding of what's going on or why. This
software mocks the notion of craftsmanship and the idea that skill
is necessary in any context. (New York Times Photo)
