Russian Communists and labor unionists lining up during a
demonstration near Red Square in Moscow on Wednesday to protest
Boris Yeltsin's rule. Along with a road block in Vladivostok, the
protests drew only a small fraction of the 10 million demonstrators
the Communists had expected. And while thousands of factories and
companies conducted short, symbolic work stoppages, life went on as
