<HEADLINE>
QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-AIDS-DEATHS, which moved in
``w'' news file.) 
c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``This is great news. But I have a 23-year-old son, and I'm
periodically shocked when he says things, like, `It's not a problem
anymore, right Mom?'''
</P>
<P>
   _ DR. GERRY McQUILLAN, epidemiologist, on the decline in AIDS
deaths.
</P>
