<HEADLINE>
KINGS TRIM ROSTER TO 24
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGER PHILLIPS  
 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Kings trimmed their roster to the regular-season limit of 24
on Wednesday, assigning injured defensemen Mark Visheau and
Jaroslav Modry to the Ice Dogs.
</P>
<P>
   Other Kings playing for the IHL team in Long Beach are goalie
Manny Legace, defenseman Jan Nemecek and forwards Jason Morgan and
Dan Bylsma. The Kings open the season Saturday in Edmonton. The Ice
Dogs open the season at 7:30 p.m. Friday against Houston at the
Long Beach Arena.
</P>
<P>
   The 6-foot-6, 235-pound Visheau, 26, had one assist and 71
penalty minutes in five exhibition appearances with the Kings. He
suffered a thumb injury in a fight with the Mighty Ducks' Stu
Grimson last week and underwent surgery this week. He is expected
to be sidelined for about two months. Visheau played for Milwaukee
in the IHL last season.
</P>
<P>
   The 6-2, 219-pound Modry, 27, has played sporadically in the NHL
and spent last year with Utah in the IHL. He appeared in two
exhibition games before suffering a bruised thigh, and is listed as
week to week.
</P>
</TEXT>
