<SLUG> BC-BBA-INDIANS-WRIGHT-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WRIGHT GETS NO GUARANTEES
</HEADLINE>
   (nk) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Jaret Wright, knocked out after two-thirds of an
inning against the Yankees in Game 1 on Tuesday night, may not get
another start in the American League Championship Series. Asked
whether Wright would pitch Game 5, Cleveland Manager Mike Hargrove
skirted the issue.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not trying to dodge your question,'' Hargrove said
Wednesday, ``but I am going to. We have got some options. I think
that I have in consideration the fact that Jaret's last two
postseason starts have not been what I think he expects himself to
be or we would like to have seen. But I think we also have to
realize that he has got tremendous stuff. I will make the decision
as we get closer to that.''
</P>
<P>
   Hargrove could start Dave Burba or Chad Ogea instead of Wright
in Game 5. Burba pitched one-third of an inning and got the victory
in Wednesday night's game, and he also pitched well in relief in
the division series against Boston, replacing Dwight Gooden in the
first inning of Game 2 after Gooden was ejected. Ogea threw
effectively after relieving Wright on Tuesday night.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
